ovement time: 30 minutes", "Use the routine below to build sleep pressure early in the day."], "whyThisWorks": "Stronger physical activity increases sleep pressure, which helps the body fall asleep faster and stay asleep longer."}, {"type": "exercise_routine", "title": "Morning movement routine", "totalDuration": "30 min", "exercises": [{"name": "Brisk Walking", "instructions": ["Walk at a steady, relaxed pace in the morning light."], "duration": "18-20 minutes continuous walking."}, {"name": "Bodyweight Squats", "instructions": ["Lower with control and stand tall through each rep."], "reps": "20 reps x 5 sets"}, {"name": "Pushups", "instructions": ["Keep your body long and your core engaged."], "reps": "15 reps x 5 sets"}, {"name": "Jumping Jacks", "instructions": ["Keep the movement rhythmic and light."], "reps": "40 reps x 4 sets"}, {"name": "Standing Forward Stretch", "instructions": ["Move slowly and breathe through each stretch."], "reps": "12 slow repetitions"}]}, {"type": "action_step", "stepNumber": 4, "title": "Caffeine Control Rule", "instructions": ["Follow this rule strictly:", "No caffeine after 2 PM", "This includes: coffee, tea, energy drinks, pre-workout drinks."], "whyThisWorks": "Caffeine can remain active in the body 6-8 hours, disturbing sleep cycles."}, {"type": "action_step", "stepNumber": 5, "title": "Evening Nervous System Downshift", "duration": "10-20 minutes.", "instructions": ["About 60 minutes before bed, listen to your guided sleep meditation audio.", "Lie comfortably in bed.", "Play the meditation audio at low volume.", "Close your eyes and follow the instructions.", "Allow the body to relax naturally."]}, {"type": "audio", "title": "Guided Sleep Meditation", "description": "A gentle bedtime audio for Day 14 that supports locking in the sleep rhythm.", "audioStoragePath": "audio/sleep/14.mp3", "durationSeconds": 900}, {"type": "action_step", "stepNumber": 6, "title": "Body Temperature Sleep Trick", "instructions": ["Take a warm shower 60-90 minutes before sleep."], "whyThisWorks": "After the shower, the body temperature drops slightly, signaling the brain that it is time for sleep."}, {"type": "action_step", "stepNumber": 7, "title": "The Military Sleep Method (Fast Sleep Technique)", "duration": "3-5 min", "instructions": ["Relax your forehead", "Relax jaw and tongue", "Drop shoulders completely", "Slowly breathe out"]}, {"type": "mindfulness_exercise", "title": "Military sleep imagery", "duration": "3-5 min", "steps": ["You are lying on a quiet beach at night.", "You hear gentle waves and feel a cool breeze.", "The night feels calm and peaceful.", "Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly.", "If thoughts appear, gently return to the scene and keep breathing slowly."], "completionMessage": "Let the scene stay soft and steady until sleep takes over."}, {"type": "mindfulness_exercise", "title": "The \"Digital Sunset Rule\"", "duration": "90 min setup", "steps": ["Screens are one of the biggest sleep disruptors.", "Create a digital sunset 90 minutes before bedtime.", "This means:", "stop using phones", "avoid social media", "avoid bright laptop screens", "avoid intense TV content", "Instead, use this time for:", "reading", "stretching", "listening to calm audio", "preparing for sleep"], "completionMessage": "Screens emit blue light, which blocks melatonin production. Reducing screen exposure before sleep allows the brain to naturally prepare for sleep."}, {"type": "close", "message": "Day 14 is complete.", "secondaryMessage": "Lock in a stable sleep rhythm and protect the brain from late-night stimulation."}]'::jsonb
)
