"Use the routine below to build sleep pressure early in the day."], "whyThisWorks": "Higher daily activity increases adenosine buildup, helping the body enter deeper sleep cycles."}, {"type": "exercise_routine", "title": "Morning movement routine", "totalDuration": "45-50 min", "exercises": [{"name": "Brisk Walking", "instructions": ["Walk at a steady, relaxed pace in the morning light."], "duration": "25-28 minutes continuous walking."}, {"name": "Bodyweight Squats", "instructions": ["Lower with control and stand tall through each rep."], "reps": "30 reps x 5 sets"}, {"name": "Pushups", "instructions": ["Keep your body long and your core engaged."], "reps": "22 reps x 5 sets"}, {"name": "Jumping Jacks", "instructions": ["Keep the movement rhythmic and light."], "reps": "60 reps x 4 sets"}, {"name": "Plank Hold", "instructions": ["Hold a straight line and keep breathing through the effort."], "duration": "50 seconds x 5 sets"}, {"name": "Standing Forward Stretch", "instructions": ["Move slowly and breathe through each stretch."], "reps": "15 slow repetitions"}]}, {"type": "action_step", "stepNumber": 4, "title": "Caffeine Control Rule", "instructions": ["Follow this rule strictly:", "No caffeine after 2 PM", "This includes: coffee, tea, energy drinks, pre-workout drinks."], "whyThisWorks": "Caffeine can remain active in the body 6-8 hours, disturbing sleep quality."}, {"type": "action_step", "stepNumber": 5, "title": "Evening Nervous System Downshift", "duration": "10-20 minutes.", "instructions": ["About 60 minutes before bed, listen to your guided sleep meditation audio.", "Lie comfortably in bed.", "Play the meditation audio at low volume.", "Close your eyes and follow the instructions.", "Allow your body to relax naturally."]}, {"type": "audio", "title": "Guided Sleep Meditation", "description": "A gentle bedtime audio for Day 19 that supports releasing hidden body tension.", "audioStoragePath": "audio/sleep/19.mp3", "durationSeconds": 900}, {"type": "action_step", "stepNumber": 6, "title": "Body Temperature Sleep Trick", "instructions": ["Take a warm shower 60-90 minutes before sleep."], "whyThisWorks": "After the shower, your body temperature drops slightly, signaling the brain that it is time for sleep."}, {"type": "action_step", "stepNumber": 7, "title": "The Military Sleep Method (Fast Sleep Technique)", "duration": "3-5 min", "instructions": ["Relax your forehead", "Relax jaw and tongue", "Drop shoulders completely", "Slowly breathe out"]}, {"type": "mindfulness_exercise", "title": "Military sleep imagery", "duration": "3-5 min", "steps": ["You are lying beside a quiet river in the mountains.", "The water flows gently and the night air is peaceful.", "Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly.", "If thoughts appear, gently return to the scene and keep breathing slowly."], "completionMessage": "Let the scene stay soft and steady until sleep takes over."}, {"type": "mindfulness_exercise", "title": "The \"Jaw Release Trick\"", "duration": "1-2 min", "steps": ["Many people hold hidden tension in the jaw muscles, which can keep the brain alert.", "While lying in bed:", "Slightly open your mouth.", "Let your tongue relax at the bottom of your mouth.", "Allow the jaw to feel loose and heavy.", "Stay like this for 1-2 minutes."], "completionMessage": "Jaw tension is connected to the brain''s stress response system. Releasing the jaw sends a signal that the body is safe and ready for sleep."}, {"type": "close", "message": "Day 19 is complete.", "secondaryMessage": "Release hidden muscle tension, allowing the body to enter deeper and more continuous sleep."}]'::jsonb
)
